AFRICAN SWINE FEVER - AFRICA (02): ZAMBIA (SOUTHERN) DOMESTIC, OIE
******************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 4 Nov 2022
Source: WOAH-WAHIS (World Animal Health Information System) 2022 [edited]
https://wahis.woah.org/#/in-review/4683


Zambia -- African swine fever virus (inf. with)
-----------------------------------------------
General information
Report type: immediate notification
Started: 7 Sep 2022 [see epidemiological comments. - Mod.CRD]
Confirmed: 20 Oct 2022
Reported: 28 Oct 2022 [published by WOAH on 4 Nov 2022. - Mod.CRD]
Reason for notification: recurrence
Last occurrence: 31 Oct 2021
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: African swine fever virus
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

Outbreak location 1: Siachitema, Chifusa, Lungunya, and Nkandanzovu Veterinary Camps, Kalomo District, Southern Province
Date of start of the outbreak: 7 Sep 2022 [see epidemiological comments. - Mod.CRD]
Epidemiological unit: other
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered or killed for commercial use / Vaccinated
Swine / 9184 / 1850 / 594 / 0 / 0 / 0

Affected population: affected pig populations were of all ages in a traditional management system within an aggregation of villages.

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: swill feeding, illegal movement of animals
Epidemiological comments: affected pig populations were of all ages in a traditional management system. Note: Another African swine fever event (4386) was ongoing in a different province of Zambia, was resolved on 30 Sep 2022, and is not epidemiologically linked to this new event which started on 7 Sep 2022. However, due to a conflict with dates, the date of the last occurrence is reported to be 1 Sep 2021 in this new event.

Control measures at event level
Domestic control measures applied: movement control; traceability; surveillance outside the restricted zone; surveillance within the restricted zone; screening.

Additional measures: stamping out

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Central Veterinary Research Institute (CVRI) (national laboratory) / swine / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 20 Oct 2022 / positive

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the WOAH report at the source URL above.

Please note that any discrepancies in event start, confirmation, and other dates in ProMED posts and the WOAH corresponding reports are the result of a technical problem already being addressed by WOAH. - Mod.CRD]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED

[Globally since 2020, and as of 20 Oct 2022, ASF has been reported in 44 countries.

The latest WOAH African swine fever (ASF) situation report 22, is available at https://www.woah.org/app/uploads/2022/10/asf-report22.pdf: "This report provides an update of the African swine fever (ASF) situation, according to the information submitted through the World Animal Health Information System of the World Organization for Animal Health (WAHIS) between 30 Sep and 20 Oct 2022."
- Mod.CRD

